00:54:36.533 --> 00:55:03.260
' I'm sitting here trying to find old things from Kathryn Kuhlman to feed on today before I did my broadcast, listening to old tent revivals from Oral Roberts and just feeding on the past and going, 'Man, when's our time?

00:55:03.260 --> 00:55:07.720
' And there has to be our time.

00:55:07.720 --> 00:55:13.724
I truly believe we're about to see the greatest harvest of souls this world has ever seen before.

00:55:13.724 --> 00:55:18.891
But it's not going to be something that we've seen before.

00:55:18.891 --> 00:55:26.550
He's going to do something that's never been seen before.

00:55:26.550 --> 00:55:27.714
Behold, he's going to do something new.

00:55:27.714 --> 00:55:39.989
But I told the Lord, I said, 'I don't want to focus on what people that are old, that have passed on, that are no longer here, did.

00:55:54.390 --> 00:55:54.860
I want to see something new in this generation.

00:55:58.960 --> 00:56:07.394
I want to see it with my sons, with my daughters, with the youth of this generation, with our young people.

00:56:07.394 --> 00:56:13.000
God, pour out your spirit one more time.

00:56:13.000 --> 00:56:18.520
Cause a major revival to flow over America.

00:56:22.301 --> 00:56:22.963
You said you were not done with America.

00:56:22.963 --> 00:56:34.965
' And this is not a revival where we go, 'Well, we rededicated America back to God.

00:56:34.965 --> 00:56:50.691
' I don't care about America being back to God; I want the church of America to be rededicated without this lukewarm church that I see.

00:56:50.691 --> 00:57:04.540
When you visit a church and you walk away not feeling stirred up, not feeling that you've got what it takes to conquer the week.

00:57:17.983 --> 00:57:26.280
When you walk away and you go, 'Well, that was a real good little whatever,' and you had some beautiful praise and worship because you've got paid musicians up there that are getting paid some of them almost six figures playing up there because they're trained musicians that are in it for the money and everything.

00:57:26.280 --> 00:57:57.360
I know a man's worthy of his hire, I'm not trying to always criticize, but I'm wanting to really emphasize: where is the true Holy Ghost church where we see the power of God flow through the auditorium and people delivered from demonic oppression and possession and the spirit of the Lord heals them from the top of their head to the soles of their feet?

00:58:01.533 --> 00:58:01.778
It's a fire shut up in my bones.

00:58:05.200 --> 00:58:08.667
And I hear some people when we talk to—because I love the South Koreans, they're some of the most beautiful-hearted praying people.

00:58:08.667 --> 00:58:12.320
I mean, my goodness, they're good folks.

00:58:12.320 --> 00:58:17.830
I love my South Korean channel.

00:58:17.840 --> 00:58:28.480
And it's amazing what the Lord has done over in South Korea with the people.

00:58:28.480 --> 00:58:30.760
They're so hungry.

00:58:48.760 --> 00:58:48.983
And I just look for the authentic.

00:58:54.080 --> 00:58:54.427
And then some of them say, 'Braden, we're experiencing that here.

00:58:54.427 --> 00:59:01.224
' We're experiencing it in Africa; there are parts of Africa where we're experiencing that.

00:59:01.224 --> 00:59:03.900
We get the emails.

00:59:03.900 --> 00:59:05.823
We're seeing revival.

00:59:05.823 --> 00:59:07.629
We're seeing this.

00:59:07.629 --> 00:59:12.091
Are you all not seeing anything like that?

00:59:12.091 --> 00:59:15.640
People are being raised from the dead.

00:59:15.640 --> 00:59:18.566
People are being healed.

00:59:18.566 --> 00:59:20.394
Blind eyes are opening.

00:59:20.394 --> 00:59:22.640
We're seeing those things.

00:59:22.640 --> 00:59:26.427
Are you not seeing that in America?

00:59:41.280 --> 00:59:41.733
I said, 'No, I don't think so.

00:59:45.806 --> 00:59:47.143
I don't see it in the circle we're in.

00:59:47.143 --> 00:59:51.852
But if it is happening, I want to be a part of it.

00:59:51.852 --> 01:00:05.055
I know I see some miracles that my friend, Billy Burke—he has healing services—but it's not like what I want to see: Acts chapter 2—raise the dead, walking on water.

01:00:12.589 --> 01:00:12.914
I mean, you know, I want to see some of that.

01:00:12.914 --> 01:00:21.520
I love it when people get healed of cancer and people's eyes get opened.

01:00:21.520 --> 01:00:23.248
It's amazing.

01:00:23.248 --> 01:00:40.926
Never lose your awe of God, but I'm wanting creative miracles: arms growing out, eyes popping back in, ears that weren't there, appendages that were not there coming back like the disciples.

01:00:40.926 --> 01:00:47.542
' And people are saying, 'Brandon, we're having that over here.

01:00:47.542 --> 01:00:51.246
' And I thought, 'What do we get to take in America?

01:00:51.246 --> 01:00:53.777
How do we have that?

01:00:53.777 --> 01:00:57.980
' I am on a mission.

01:00:57.980 --> 01:01:13.880
I was cleaning out my garage and blowing out the leaves from the winter and doing things, and the Lord stirred in my spirit: 'What does it take to see the dead raised when you need to see it raised?

01:01:27.880 --> 01:01:28.060
When you see somebody you love die or they're not here anymore and you know that there's Lazarus moments coming, that though you were dead yet shall you live.

01:01:28.060 --> 01:01:46.760
' When there's an anointing that needs to be pulled on and you see desperation in someone's eyes, is it there to bring forth the miracle that they're believing for, to pull on that anointing?

01:01:46.760 --> 01:01:48.060
What does it take?

01:01:53.970 --> 01:02:06.440
And I go over things that I hear my elder generals talk about, like Billy and Billy, both Billies, and they talk about the sufferings and sharing His suffering and the greater glory and things that are attached to it.

01:02:12.080 --> 01:02:12.267
And I just go, 'Lord, show me.

01:02:13.013 --> 01:02:29.004
What is the switch to flip on the light in the darkness, that Your light is shining on our face like Moses, that when they see us, we're wall-to-wall Holy Ghost?

01:02:29.004 --> 01:02:46.123
' But it's not just something that we confess and we're parroting something, but it's actual manifestation that when we walk in the room, the shadow touches and they're healed and they rise up and walk.

01:02:46.123 --> 01:03:00.260
When the anointing that was on the disciples is tangible on us and it's not something that we just experience once, but we walk in it on a day-to-day basis.

01:03:09.840 --> 01:03:10.024
What is it that takes that?

01:03:10.024 --> 01:03:10.944
Is it the persecution?

01:03:10.944 --> 01:03:35.676
Because when I was praying for Africa and we were on here praying and we saw the people of Nigeria, I believe it was, and I saw their flag, and the Lord said, 'The greater the persecution, the greater the anointing.

01:03:35.676 --> 01:03:43.133
The greater the persecution, the greater the presence and the power and the glory comes with the anointing.

01:03:43.133 --> 01:03:47.743
For these sufferings bring forth the greater glory.

01:03:47.743 --> 01:03:51.040
' When Paul and Silas...

01:03:51.040 --> 01:03:59.970
Peter was in the prison, and then you have these moments where the church prayed and they interceded and they were able to get the gates opened.

01:04:01.890 --> 01:04:04.540
They were able, with guards on both sides watching over them in the middle of the prison.

01:04:16.007 --> 01:04:16.253
And they didn't want, because they knew that they had some kind of supernatural ability and they had been assigned these guards on both sides.

01:04:21.413 --> 01:04:21.680
And Peter's asleep knowing that tomorrow he's going to die.

01:04:21.680 --> 01:04:30.730
I don't know about you, but if I get some kind of bad report, it's hard to sleep sometimes.

01:04:32.580 --> 01:04:33.360
You go, 'Oh, man,' because your mind's running.

01:04:52.200 --> 01:04:52.784
But you have so much confidence and you're so fully persuaded that you're in the prison and you're snoring and an angel has to wake you up: 'Get up!

01:04:55.700 --> 01:04:56.280
Get up!

01:04:56.280 --> 01:05:08.400
' But the prayers of the saints—why we have this channel—the prayers of the early church had enough to get the guards knocked out, open the prison door, open the gate, and get him free.

01:05:08.400 --> 01:05:14.700
What kind of prayer, what kind of intercession does it take to open a gate?

01:05:23.920 --> 01:05:24.080
A supernatural opening of the gate?

01:05:33.324 --> 01:05:38.458
What kind of prayer does it take to open the prison door?

01:05:38.458 --> 01:05:46.496
When someone's wrongly being accused in these last days, what kind of prayer does it take for a church to bring forth just a little revival and some fire in your church?

01:06:08.731 --> 01:06:09.063
That it's not church usual, it's church unusual.

01:06:19.285 --> 01:06:19.510
And that's what I'm just like, because the Lord said, 'What are you looking for?

01:06:19.510 --> 01:06:21.150
' I said, 'I'm looking for more.

01:06:21.150 --> 01:06:26.067
I'm not satisfied with the status quo.

01:06:29.175 --> 01:06:29.360
I am so done with church usual.

01:06:29.360 --> 01:06:31.460
I want church unusual.

01:06:31.460 --> 01:06:38.063
I want to see fire shut up in my bones.

01:06:49.107 --> 01:06:49.320
I want to see what Oral Roberts saw.

01:06:49.320 --> 01:06:58.080
And I want to see and experience more than what Kathryn Kuhlman experienced.

01:06:58.080 --> 01:07:02.164
If not, I said, if not, then why not?

01:07:02.164 --> 01:07:02.840
Why not me?

01:07:02.840 --> 01:07:03.387
Why then?

01:07:03.387 --> 01:07:03.751
What?

01:07:16.967 --> 01:07:18.150
You know, Lord, I know they went through things.

01:07:18.160 --> 01:07:26.907
I know I've been through some things, but Lord, what turns on that switch?

01:07:26.907 --> 01:07:47.935
Because the only thing that's ever going to change America is whenever the sons and the daughters, us, become who we're called to be and rise up and stop trying to just always pray for revival, but let revival start with us and say, 'Here am I, Lord.

01:07:47.935 --> 01:07:50.990
Send me.

01:07:51.000 --> 01:07:54.040
' But don't send me with no power.

01:07:56.505 --> 01:07:57.230
I want them to marvel at the ignorance of Brandon Biggs.

01:07:57.230 --> 01:08:01.618
Whenever he speaks, they go, 'He has been with Jesus.

01:08:01.618 --> 01:08:06.970
' There's something different about him.

01:08:06.970 --> 01:08:08.430
Why?

01:08:08.430 --> 01:08:14.933
It's not about giving glory to Brandon, but there's something different about what's on that man.

01:08:17.952 --> 01:08:18.264
And it's Jesus.

01:08:18.264 --> 01:08:20.433
Because he had been with Jesus.

01:08:20.433 --> 01:08:23.788
They marveled because they knew they were unlearned and ignorant men.

01:08:24.359 --> 01:08:26.387
But they knew they had been with Jesus.

01:08:26.387 --> 01:08:27.599
How'd they know that?

01:08:27.599 --> 01:08:30.400
Because the glory was there.

01:08:36.058 --> 01:08:36.916
The manifested presence was there.

01:08:36.916 --> 01:08:43.857
Because when God shows up on the scene, He changes the atmosphere.

01:08:44.474 --> 01:08:51.928
And when you go into a church and the atmosphere is dull, like touching a cold stove, and it's week after week...

01:08:51.928 --> 01:09:06.248
I'm not trying to pick at the church I used to work for, but week after week you go into a church and you go, 'I work here.

01:09:14.960 --> 01:09:15.480
I get a check here, but it is dead as touching a cold stove.

01:09:15.480 --> 01:09:20.458
' And yet people are getting blessed by it because you've got somebody playing some good music or whatever sermons.

01:09:20.458 --> 01:09:20.983
Okay.

01:09:29.240 --> 01:09:29.606
But I go, 'Why are we playing church?

01:09:29.606 --> 01:09:32.948
' God came to save and set the captives free.

01:09:32.948 --> 01:09:35.075
'I come to save that which was lost.

01:09:35.075 --> 01:09:47.458
' And now in Acts 4, this is my favorite: 'Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and perceived that they were unlearned and ignorant men, they marveled and took knowledge of them that they had been with Jesus.

01:09:47.458 --> 01:09:51.388
' It's not just being with Him one time.

01:09:51.388 --> 01:09:56.410
It's being with Him day after day, sitting at His feet and having a relationship with Him.

01:09:56.820 --> 01:09:58.729
I told you more people would go home.

01:09:58.729 --> 01:10:01.611
James Robison went home yesterday.

01:10:01.611 --> 01:10:03.690
We have more generals going home.

01:10:36.265 --> 01:10:36.440
And the Lord said there will be a changing of the guard, a passing of the baton in the days ahead.

01:10:37.424 --> 01:10:41.924
And you're going to see the major generals that have been in the past start to transition home.

01:10:50.520 --> 01:10:50.707
He said, 'I'm raising up new voices.

01:10:58.429 --> 01:10:58.754
I'm raising up a new generation.

01:11:08.580 --> 01:11:08.745
I'm raising up new generals to those that I've called that say, "Yes, here am I, Lord, send me.

01:11:08.745 --> 01:11:09.440
" You're the closers.

01:11:09.440 --> 01:11:19.684
' They had their time and this generation is going to start to go home.

01:11:43.095 --> 01:11:43.470
And the Lord said, 'You're going to see more and more of it through the summer.

01:11:43.470 --> 01:11:53.760
' We just had another one, a third one: Marilyn Hickey, Joni, and now Pat—and I only say, 'Well, who's next?

01:11:53.760 --> 01:11:55.210
' I don't know.

01:11:55.210 --> 01:11:58.705
But there are going to be more transitions.

01:11:58.705 --> 01:12:01.280
I saw certain major ministries going home.

01:12:01.280 --> 01:12:04.400
Some of them huge, huge ministries.

01:12:11.560 --> 01:12:11.991
And it will get world attention.

01:12:11.991 --> 01:12:12.853
Huge.

01:12:15.440 --> 01:12:16.383
And Pat Robertson was a huge ministry.

01:12:16.383 --> 01:12:18.943
Joni, I mean, they're all pretty...

01:12:18.943 --> 01:12:32.537
they were all pretty big ministries.

01:12:32.537 --> 01:12:38.213
" Marilyn Hickey, all of them.

01:12:38.213 --> 01:12:42.580
So, we see a transition.

01:12:42.580 --> 01:12:49.920
When people step out and go home, there's a void.

01:12:54.656 --> 01:12:55.104
One needs to rise up.

01:12:55.104 --> 01:12:57.311
Will you be that person?

01:12:57.311 --> 01:13:02.920
They're up there rooting for us right now.

01:13:02.920 --> 01:13:08.720
Their cloud of witnesses say, 'Will you help finish the race?

01:13:08.720 --> 01:13:12.120
Don't let the baton drop.

01:13:12.120 --> 01:13:17.920
Keep running with this end-time army.

01:13:17.920 --> 01:13:23.160
' And I know there's more going home soon.

01:13:31.580 --> 01:13:32.650
The Lord said it; He told me.

01:13:32.650 --> 01:13:45.274
He said specific ones to me, and I've never—don't make that public.

01:13:45.274 --> 01:14:00.333
So I just want to stir you up today to not give up on your dreams of what God's called you to do just because you didn't see it manifest in the first years of when you thought it should.

01:14:00.333 --> 01:14:10.520
God knows when you're able to handle it, and when the time is, and when it's time for you to rise up and be who you need to be.

01:14:10.520 --> 01:14:11.429
Humble yourself.

01:14:11.429 --> 01:14:17.920
Even if it's to say, 'Hey, I'm going to go volunteer at a church and be a janitor.

01:14:17.920 --> 01:14:22.448
Do whatever it takes to get the gospel out.

01:14:22.448 --> 01:14:31.469
' Diana, we were talking about it when we worked at the church.

01:14:39.337 --> 01:14:39.531
The guest speaker usually gets the most praise.

01:14:39.531 --> 01:14:41.915
They get in late, they leave early.

01:14:46.989 --> 01:14:50.480
The janitor, like me—I was cleaning the bathrooms until sometimes 1:00 or 2:00 in the morning after the service.

01:14:58.318 --> 01:14:59.677
You go in there and it's dark.

01:15:46.080 --> 01:15:49.435
It's like crickets, and you set up the chairs, you vacuum the aisles, you're making sure all the diapers are cleaned out of the nurseries, and you do that time and time again—the least thanked position.

01:15:49.435 --> 01:16:21.680
But without that janitor, without that offering counter, without the usher, without the greeter, without the parking lot attendant, without the nursery worker, that guest speaker or whoever it was for the revival couldn't have gotten the job done the way they did.

01:16:21.680 --> 01:16:46.800
Because if the bathrooms were stinky, the floors had urine on them, somebody just took a dump all over the stool, you've got all this nasty stuff going on, and you're going, 'This is the stinkiest bathroom I ever walked in,' and you go, 'I don't even want to go into that church and listen to this guy.

01:16:46.800 --> 01:17:18.000
' Don't ever underestimate the importance of who you are and how you bring forth the atmosphere for that person to receive what Jesus is about to speak through that speaker.

01:17:18.000 --> 01:17:21.550
Your part was just as important as the speaker's was.

01:17:39.040 --> 01:18:18.333
And I remember setting up the chairs, cleaning up the vomit when somebody wrote poo on the wall, wipe their booty on my wall and write it out in numbers—'poo' or whatever they want to say, just being disgusting with their feces, doing some of the most filthy, vile things I've ever seen in a bathroom.

01:18:26.413 --> 01:18:26.689
I cleaned it for 15 years of my life.

01:18:38.275 --> 01:18:59.435
And I remember every single time going home and thinking, 'Man, I just wanted to make it where if they came in and it smelled good, if they walked into the bathroom and it didn't smell like stuff or nurseries or whatever and their kids didn't go home sick and they said, "Our kids always come to church and play on the church equipment and they're always leaving with a cold or a virus because they spread it around.

01:18:59.435 --> 01:19:10.360
"' I kept even the church nursery toys clean with bleach and whatever, making sure they didn't spread viruses around during flu season.

01:19:10.360 --> 01:19:14.754
Always trying to think outside the box.

01:19:14.754 --> 01:19:25.057
If my kid was in here, how do you make sure that the virus from these flu bugs kids are passing around stays out?

01:19:25.057 --> 01:19:32.920
Always going the extra mile, making it so if you don't show up, they're going to notice.

01:19:38.280 --> 01:19:41.120
And there's many of you that may do that right now at your church.

01:19:41.120 --> 01:19:43.229
And I'm telling you, it's all hands on deck.

01:19:43.229 --> 01:19:51.440
Never ever take your position of what God's called you to do lightly.

01:20:02.964 --> 01:20:03.569
For if it wasn't for people like you, the job wouldn't be done as effective as it should have been.

01:20:08.591 --> 01:20:25.303
And I'm trying to tell you right now, the same reward that the person's going to get up there preaching with the fire—you think, 'Oh boy, they've got it all made'—man, great is the reward of those that do what we've done.

01:20:29.549 --> 01:20:37.460
The person who counts the offerings, the person who makes sure the bills are paid so that the lights are on when they showed up, making sure the water bill was paid so the toilet would flush.

01:20:37.460 --> 01:20:46.510
Never take for granted what God has called you to do and do it with all your heart.

01:20:46.510 --> 01:20:49.422
That's what we did and we continue to do.

01:21:01.280 --> 01:21:01.707
I still feel like I'm the janitor.

01:21:05.960 --> 01:21:15.874
I still feel like my wife is the offering counter and the data entry person, always behind the scenes trying just to make it.

01:21:15.874 --> 01:21:24.491
Be thankful for where you are and know that your reward is great when you get on the other side.

01:21:24.491 --> 01:21:29.754
Keep your head up.

01:21:29.754 --> 01:21:37.307
And that's my message for what I felt in my heart tonight.

01:21:51.267 --> 01:21:52.053
I said, 'Lord, what is it going to take?

01:21:52.053 --> 01:21:55.863
I'm so hungry for authentic.

01:21:55.863 --> 01:22:03.011
I'm so hungry, desperate for a true move of God.

01:22:03.011 --> 01:22:17.993
' And I'm so tired of parrots—parrots on the internet, parrots with people that just say something because they heard it from a Jack Coe meeting and you look at it and you go, 'That's truly not who you are.

01:22:17.993 --> 01:22:19.564
' And you are really fake.

01:22:28.600 --> 01:22:28.800
I want to see signs; follow them that believe.

01:22:41.656 --> 01:22:41.920
So, I stay in my little place where I'm at.

01:22:41.920 --> 01:22:50.000
You know, a lot of people invite me to go do a lot of stuff.

01:22:50.000 --> 01:23:01.234
I've had some of the biggest businessmen, some of the richest people in the United States or world contact me.

01:23:01.234 --> 01:23:05.200
And I don't know what to do with some of this.

01:23:05.200 --> 01:23:07.217
'What am I?

01:23:07.217 --> 01:23:08.246
I'm just Brandon.

01:23:08.246 --> 01:23:11.892
' They tell me, 'Brandon, you got to watch it.

01:23:17.158 --> 01:23:18.075
You got big politicians watching you all the time—senators and governors and mayors.

01:23:18.075 --> 01:23:21.360
' And I'm like, 'Why?

01:23:21.360 --> 01:23:22.512
I'm just Brandon.

01:23:22.512 --> 01:23:27.640
' And I always stay—the Lord always says, 'Stay small in your own eyes.

01:23:27.640 --> 01:23:29.800
Never get a big head.

01:23:29.800 --> 01:23:32.075
Keep your eyes on me, son.

01:23:32.075 --> 01:23:32.780
Stay vertical.

01:23:32.780 --> 01:23:39.745
No matter how much they persecute you, they're going to hate you because they hated me.

01:23:39.745 --> 01:23:43.957
They're going to curse you because they cursed me.

01:23:43.957 --> 01:24:32.570
' And I say, if that's all you got to deal with—some internet trolls, some people who think they're something, they're trying to be something—if all you deal with are some people with small brains and they want to criticize all the time because they aren't getting anyone saved, they're not getting anyone healed, they're not doing anything other than causing a ruckus and chaos in the internet community trying to be watchdogs and police dogs where they want to be because they think they're doing something.

01:24:41.100 --> 01:24:41.335
All they're doing is just being trolls.

01:24:55.733 --> 01:24:55.920
And you look at them and go, 'Why don't you put your energy into getting people saved?

01:24:55.920 --> 01:24:58.000
We're running out of time.

01:24:58.000 --> 01:25:03.491
People are dying and going to hell all around you.

01:25:03.491 --> 01:25:08.635
' And people, all they want to do is criticize and be mean.

01:25:08.635 --> 01:25:17.693
Stop being Sister Clipboard and get out and save that which was lost.

01:25:17.693 --> 01:25:20.680
We had over 600 people saved last week.

01:25:21.800 --> 01:25:25.020
You don't agree with some of the things I say?

01:25:25.020 --> 01:25:29.031
Fine, go watch somebody else.

01:25:29.031 --> 01:25:46.867
But at least we're trying to get people saved, to get people delivered, to tell them that their marriage is going to be okay because the divorce rate is as high as it's been in years.

01:25:46.867 --> 01:25:49.560
People are leaving and getting divorced.

01:25:49.560 --> 01:25:54.880
We get the emails: 'I don't want to be with him anymore.

01:25:54.880 --> 01:25:55.720
' Why?

01:25:55.720 --> 01:25:58.240
'Well, I don't really have a reason.

01:25:58.240 --> 01:26:05.264
I just don't love him anymore.

01:26:05.264 --> 01:26:09.560
' Well, he didn't commit adultery on you.

01:26:09.560 --> 01:26:09.937
No.

01:26:09.937 --> 01:26:10.880
He's not beating you?

01:26:10.880 --> 01:26:19.080
No, I just don't love him anymore.

01:26:19.080 --> 01:26:23.990
Well, that's not a reason to get a divorce.

01:26:23.990 --> 01:26:27.697
Find what you were in love with before.

01:26:27.697 --> 01:26:28.872
How did you get...

01:26:44.520 --> 01:26:44.671
what was it all based out of lust and sex and everything?

01:26:44.671 --> 01:26:45.276
'I don't know.

01:26:45.276 --> 01:26:47.560
We never had a foundation.

01:26:47.560 --> 01:26:49.720
It was just always about physical.

01:26:49.720 --> 01:26:55.223
' There are people that you just listen to them and you go, 'Find God in your marriage.

01:26:55.223 --> 01:26:58.480
Put God first in your marriage.

01:26:58.480 --> 01:26:59.080
Pray together.

01:26:59.080 --> 01:27:00.680
Read your Bible together.

01:27:00.680 --> 01:27:02.100
Take communion together.

01:27:02.100 --> 01:27:06.453
Do things together that stir you up spiritually.

01:27:06.453 --> 01:27:08.045
Listen to a sermon together.

01:27:08.045 --> 01:27:08.726
Go on a date.

01:27:08.726 --> 01:27:11.951
Hey, let's go out and see a movie.

01:27:11.951 --> 01:27:14.671
' Let's go out and look at the lake.

01:27:19.533 --> 01:27:23.870
But don't give up on something that is beautiful just because you say, "Well, I fell out of love with them.

01:27:23.870 --> 01:27:28.903
" Find scripture that pertains to what you're going through.

01:27:28.903 --> 01:27:30.640
Love never fails.

